Privacy Policy

1. Introduction

This Privacy Policy outlines the principles of processing user data for the InfiniNote: Capture Everything application ("Application"). The Application is available through the Google Play Store and uses Google AdMob advertising services.

2. Data Controller

The data controller for user personal data is Alan Pawlukiewicz based at N/A (Individual Developer). If you have any questions regarding the processing of personal data, please contact us at alanp.apps.contact@gmail.com.

3. Scope of Collected Data

The Application may collect and process the following user data:

Device identifiers and anonymous data regarding Application usage,

Information about advertisements displayed in the Application,

Analytical and diagnostic data, automatically collected by Google AdMob and Google Play,

Access to notifications to inform users about important updates within the Application,

Access to the device's camera, used exclusively for adding photos to notes within the Application.

The Application may collect and process the following user data:

Device identifiers and anonymous data regarding Application usage,

Information about advertisements displayed in the Application,

Analytical and diagnostic data, automatically collected by Google AdMob and Google Play.

4. Purpose of Data Processing

The collected data is used for the following purposes:

Displaying personalized advertisements through Google AdMob,

Improving the quality and functionality of the Application,

Analyzing application usage to optimize its performance,

Sending notifications to keep users informed about important updates and reminders,

Allowing users to add photos to notes using the device's camera; no images are stored on external servers.

The collected data is used for the following purposes:

Displaying personalized advertisements through Google AdMob,

Improving the quality and functionality of the Application,

Analyzing application usage to optimize its performance.

5. Google AdMob and Cookies

The Application uses Google AdMob to display ads. Google AdMob may use cookies and other tracking technologies to personalize ad content and analyze ad performance. Detailed information on how Google processes data can be found in Google's Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy.

6. Sharing Personal Data

We do not sell or share users' personal data with third parties, except for:

Entities providing analytical and advertising services (e.g., Google AdMob),

Law enforcement and public administration authorities, if required by law.

7. Data Security

We take user data security seriously by implementing appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect against unauthorized access, loss, or improper processing.

8. User Rights

Users have the right to:

Access their data,

Request correction or deletion of their data,

Restrict the processing of their data,

Object to data processing,

Disable notifications at any time through their device settings,

Revoke camera access through their device settings,

File a complaint with the data protection authority.

Users have the right to:

Access their data,

Request correction or deletion of their data,

Restrict the processing of their data,

Object to data processing,

File a complaint with the data protection authority.

9. Changes to the Privacy Policy

The Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. Any changes will be published within the Application and will take effect upon publication.

10. Contact

If you have any questions regarding this Privacy Policy, please contact us at alanp.apps.contact@gmail.com.
